The paper proposes a method for interactive segmentation of 3D medical volumes using a combination of sampling techniques and machine learning. This involves the use of probability maps, shape priors, and consistency with previous answers to progressively segment an organ. Given the focus on computer vision and machine learning techniques, as well as the use of medical imaging data, it is likely that this paper belongs to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of machine learning techniques and the focus on optimization suggest that the paper may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of medical imaging data and the focus on segmentation also suggest that the paper may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of sampling techniques and the focus on optimization suggest that the paper may also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
